(42, 14, 25, 43, 6, 24, 27, 'great multitudes with him', 'Seeking Jesus and True Sustenance', 'Both passages emphasize the act of seeking Jesus. In Luke, the multitudes follow him, while in John, the people seek him after the miracle of the loaves. This connection highlights the distinction between seeking Jesus for physical needs versus spiritual sustenance.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
